# Chat Handoff (Always)

## When to tell user: switch to new chat

Proactively say **SWITCH CHAT** (one clear line) when any of these hit:

1. **Topic change** — new feature/bug unrelated to current thread
2. **Milestone done** — feature/fix/docs unit finished; next work is different
3. **Context bloat** — long thread (~15+ back-and-forth) or replies get repetitive/confused
4. **Agent drift** — wrong architecture, forgotten vault rules, or re-asking solved facts
5. **After big vault/rule change** — Brain OS / always-on rules updated; fresh chat loads rules clean
6. **User asks** — “handoff”, “new chat”, “context for next chat”

Do **not** nag every turn. Once per trigger. Prefer switch over stuffing more into a dying thread.

## Before SWITCH CHAT

1. Update `docs/knowledge/15_MEMORY/Current-Context.md` (Today / Working on / Next step / files)
2. Write `docs/knowledge/15_MEMORY/Handoff-Latest.md` with the handoff pack below
3. Paste the same pack in chat inside a single copy-ready fenced block

## Handoff message format (generate exactly)

```text
AIIMIN handoff — paste as first message in new chat

Read first:
1. docs/knowledge/00_HOME.md
2. docs/knowledge/15_MEMORY/Current-Context.md
3. docs/knowledge/15_MEMORY/Handoff-Latest.md

Done this chat:
- <bullet outcomes>

Still open:
- <bullet next tasks>

Touch only if needed:
- <paths>

Constraints:
- Vault-first. No whole-repo scan.
- Palette lock. Mobile /m = capture only.
- No auth/schema change unless I ask.
- Commit only if I ask.

Next action:
- <one concrete first step>
```

Keep handoff ≤40 lines. No secrets. No code dumps — paths + vault pointers only.

## User triggers

On `handoff` / `new chat context` / `switch chat`: run the before-SWITCH steps even if no other trigger fired.
